  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, CvParamListCapable, MzQuantMLObject, ParamCapable

    public class SearchDatabase
extends ExternalData
implements Serializable, ParamCapable, CvParamListCapable
    A database used for searching mass spectra. Examples include a set of amino acid sequence entries, or annotated spectra libraries.

      • getCvParam

        public List<CvParam> getCvParam()
        Gets the value of the cvParam property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the cvParam property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getCvParam().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list CvParam

        Specified by:
        getCvParam in interface CvParamListCapable
        Returns:
        A List of CvParam objects.
